New Records: Harry Kane scored twice in his 100th game for England
Harry Kane became the first England player to score in his 100th game
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored the first goal with a powerful shot that clipped the crossbar
Harry Kane scored the second goal with an assist from Noni Madueke
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley could remain as interim manager for the next international break
England is level on six points at the top of their Nations League group
